Secondly, the gray box is the parent of the other two divs, so it is always going to be underneath them, unless you take the child divs completely out of the flow, and give them a negative z-index. For example, I&#39;ve given the black and red boxes a `position:absolute`, and changed the gray box to the default `position: static`, so the red and black box are not being treated like children of the gray box anymore:

